Rigidity (The design is difficult to change)
Fragility (The design is easy to break)
Immobility (The design is difficult to reuse)
Viscosity (It is difficult to do the right thing, easy to do the wrong thing),
Needless complexity (Overdesign)
Needless repetition (Mouse abuse, copy and paste)
Opacity (Disorganized expression, unreadable code)

often paired with a fibonacci number representing the scale of the problem.
